  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (3fc1491 2022-06-06T09:52:25.986569Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge remappings\n\n### Operating System\n\nWindows\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI attempted to do:\r\n```bash\r\nforge remappings > remappings.txt\r\n```\r\nwhich works and outputs the following:\r\n```\r\nds-test/=lib\\forge-std\\lib\\ds-test\\src/\r\nforge-std/=lib\\forge-std\\src/\r\n```\r\nBut if you now do forge build or forge test, I get this:\r\n```\r\n(base) PS D:\\insurance-project> forge remappings > remappings.txt\r\n(base) PS D:\\insurance-project> forge build\r\nconfig error: stream did not contain valid UTF-8 in Remapping Provider\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  failed to extract foundry config\r\nLocation: config\\src\\lib.rs:355\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n(base) PS D:\\insurance-project> forge test\r\nError: \r\n   0: stream did not contain valid UTF-8 in Remapping Provider\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   cli\\src\\cmd\\forge\\test.rs:291\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n(base) PS D:\\insurance-project> \r\n```\r\n\r\nAlso, if you just simply execute forge remappings standalone, you receive the same error:\r\n```\r\n(base) PS D:\\insurance-project> forge remappings\r\nconfig error: stream did not contain valid UTF-8 in Remapping Provider\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  failed to extract foundry config\r\nLocation: config\\src\\lib.rs:355\r\nBacktrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n```\r\n\r\nWithout a remappings.txt file, forge build & test work fine.",
